Package com.genologics.ri.processexecution

Class Summary
ArtifactBase The base representation of an Artifact in the context of Process execution, defining common elements for both input and output Artifacts.
ExecutableInputOutputMap Processes link inputs to outputs and this relationship is called an input-output map.
ExecutableProcess The process element defines the XML needed to run a process.
Input The input element provides URIs to one or more Artifacts that will be used by the Process.
InstrumentLink The instrument element provides a URI to the instrument that is responsible for running the process.
ObjectFactory This object contains factory methods for each Java content interface and Java element interface generated in the com.genologics.ri.processexecution package.
Output The output element provides information about the Artifacts that will be created by the Process.
Parameter The parameter is a child element of process execution that integrates the Process with the External Program Integration plug-in (EPP).
Technician The technician element provides a URI to the user that is responsible for the Process.
 

Enum Summary
QCFlag
